d.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20late%20summer%202022%20was%20also%20proving%20a%20'devastating%20period'%20for%20Russian%20forces%20in%20Ukraine.%20Ukrainian%20forces%20were%20advancing%20on%20Russian-occupied%20Kherson%20in%20the%20south%2C%20the%20city%20which%20had%20been%20Russia's%20biggest%20prize%20since%20the%20invasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20these%20Ukrainian%20forces%20advanced%2C%20entire%20Russian%20units%20were%20in%20danger%20of%20being%20surrounded.%20The%20view%20inside%20the%20administration%20was%20that%20such%20a%20catastrophic%20loss%20could%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bpotential%20trigger%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20use%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%2C%20according%20to%20CNN.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Russia%20was%20allegedly%20circulating%20a%20new%20%26quot%3Bfalse%20flag%20story%26quot%3B%20about%20a%20Ukrainian%20dirty%20bomb%2C%20which%20US%20officials%20feared%20could%20be%20intended%20as%20a%20cover%20for%20a%20Russian%20nuclear%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202022%2C%20Russia's%20defence%20minister%2C%20Sergei%20Shoigu%2C%20made%20a%20series%20of%20phone%20calls%20to%20defence%20officials%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20France%20and%20Turkey%2C%20telling%20them%20that%20the%20Kremlin%20was%20%26quot%3Bconcerned%20about%20possible%20provocations%20by%20Kyiv%20involving%20the%20use%20of%20a%20dirty%20bomb.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20it%20is%20pertinent%20to%20note%20that%20at%20no%20time%20did%20the%20US%20detect%20intelligence%20indicating%20Russia%20was%20taking%20steps%20to%20mobilize%20its%20nuclear%20forces%20to%20carry%20out%20such%20an%20attack%2C%20CNN%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20obviously%20placed%20a%20high%20priority%20on%20tracking%20and%20had%20some%20ability%20at%20least%20to%20track%20such%20movements%20of%20its%20nuclear%20forces%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20senior%20administration%20official%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20at%20no%20point%20did%20we%20ever%20see%20any%20