to%20something.%20After%20sharing%20a%20bed%20for%20the%20first%2010%20years%20of%20our%20relationship%2C%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20decided%20sleeping%20separately%20was%20a%20better%20option.%20Our%20bond%20has%20grown%20stronger%20since%20our%20%26quot%3Bsleep%20divorce.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESleep%20divorce%20is%20when%20couples%20decide%20to%20sleep%20in%20separate%20beds%2C%20or%20even%20separate%20rooms.%20It's%20an%20alternative%20growing%20in%20popularity%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-start-sleeping-in-separate-beds-sleep-divorce-2023-7%5C%22%3Eone-third%20of%20American%20couples%20choosing%20separate%20beds%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20are%20many%20reasons%20to%20go%20this%20route%2C%20from%20having%20different%20schedules%20and%20preferences%20to%20managing%20sleep%20disorders.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcameron-diaz-couples-sleeping-separate-bedrooms-relationship-2023-12%5C%22%3EEven%20Cameron%20Diaz%20is%20a%20strong%20proponent%20of%20%26quot%3Bsleep%20divorce%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20sleep%20reporter%2C%20I'll%20cover%20my%20reasons%20for%20sleeping%20separately%20from%20my%20wife%2C%20how%20to%20make%20it%20work%2C%20and%20some%20alternatives%20to%20sleep%20divorce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20we%20sleep%20in%20separate%20beds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20test%20a%20new%20mattress%20every%20two%20weeks.%20This%20is%20about%20how%20long%20it%20takes%20to%20get%20acclimated%20to%20a%20new%20mattress%2C%20which%20means%20there's%20a%20significant%20break-in%20period%20when%20I%20may%20not%20sleep%20well.%20I%20put%20myself%20through%20this%20to%20help%20you%20make%20better%20buying%20decision.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20my%20wife%20isn't%20a%20sleep%20reporter%20and%20doesn't%20want%20the%20constant%20upheaval.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20relatably%2C%20we%20also%20have%20different%20sleep%20schedules.%20I%20get%20up%20early%20and%20work%20out%20before%20my%209-to-5%20job.%20She%20likes%20to%20stay%20up%20late%20and%20sleep%20in.%20With%20our%20schedules%2C%20we%20used%20to%20risk%20disturbing%20each%20other%20as%20we%20got%20into%20and%20out%20of%20bed.%20Not%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20likes%20to%20warm%20and%20cozy%20while%20sleeping%20and%20prefers%20pets%20in%20her%20bed.%20I%20want%20to%20be%20left%20alone%2C%20pet-free%2C%20with%20no%20one%20touching%20me%20while%20I%20sleep.%20I%20overheat%20at%20night%2C%20and%20another's%20body%20heat%20compounds%20my%20discomfort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESleeping%20separately%20is%20healthy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20justifications%20for%20sleep%20divorce%20are%20not%20exhaustive.%20Other%20motivations%20include%20one%20or%20both%20partners%20having%20conditions%20like%20restless%20legs%20or%20breathing%20issues%20like%20COPD%20or%20snoring.%20Couples%20with%20drastically%20different%20mattress%20preferences%20may%20also%20want%20to%20sleep%20in%20separate%20beds%20catering%20to%20their%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BForty%20percent%20of%20my%20patients%20tend%20to%20sleep%20in%20a%20separate%20room%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr.%20Logan%20Schneider%2C%20clinical%20assistant%20professor%20of%20sleep%20medicine%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstanfordhealthcare.org%2Fmedical-clinics%2Fsleep-medicine-center.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStanford%20Sleep%20Medicine%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20treats%20patients%20with%20various%20sleep%20conditions%2C%20including%20sleep%20apnea%20and%20restless%20legs%20syndrome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rebecca-robbins.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERebecca%20Robbins%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20associate%20scientist%20at%20Brigham%20and%20Women's%20Hospital%20and%20instructor%20at%20Harvard%20Medical%20School%2C%20wants%20to%20end%20the%20stigma%20of%20sleep%20divorce.%20%26quot%3BPrioritizing%20sleep%20is%20really%20critical%20for%20couples%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Robbins.%20%26quot%3BIf%20it%20means%20sleeping%20in%20different%20bedrooms%2C%20either%20because%20one%20partner%20snores%20or%20one%20partner%20isn't%20happy%20with%20the%20mattress%2C%20then%20that%20is%20absolutely%20OK.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20noted%20that%20beyond%20cuddling%20before%20bedtime%2C%20you're%20not%20spending%20quality%20time%20with%20your%20partner%20when%20sleeping.%20That%20time%20is%20best%20for%20rest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20Ann%20and%20Dave%20Weiss%2C%20co-founders%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Db3bda5a566e920d8b05299a48bedfbb6f230778aa18c2a8c8476358cb20951ab%26postID%3D65e735fa68a8d2c26bf28e4d%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fsleep-divorce-sleeping-separately-advice%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.hatch.co%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHatch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20makers%20of%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-wake-up-light-alarm-clock%5C%22%3Ebest%20sunrise%20alarm%20clocks%3C%2Fa%3E%20we've%20tested%2C%20are%20proponents%20of%20sleep%20divorce.%20They%20sleep%20in%20separate%20rooms%20and%20have%20found%20it%20strengthens%20their%20marriage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20we%20make%20sleep%20divorce%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20beds%20are%20displayed%20in%20an%20oddly%20shaped%20bedroom.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e78aaf6080194819fcce3d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhile%20many%20sleep%20divorc%C3%A9es%20sleep%20in%20separate%20rooms%2C%20we've%20found%20two%20beds%20in%20the%20same%20room%2C%20the%20Bedsroom%2C%20work%20best%20for%20us.%3Cp%3EJames%20Brains%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%