s-why-stocks-dont-need-rate-cuts-in-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%20sent%20to%20his%20firm's%20clients.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFisher%20pointed%20to%20the%20strength%20in%20stocks%20in%202023%2C%20when%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20soared%20more%20than%2020%25%20after%20hitting%20a%20bottom%20in%20October%202022.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20economy%20has%20continued%20to%20remain%20resilient%2C%20with%20GDP%20growing%203.1%25%20over%20the%20fourth%20quarter%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bea.gov%2Fnews%2F2024%2Fgross-domestic-product-fourth-quarter-and-year-2023-advance-estimate%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMeasured%2520from%2520the%2520fourth%2520quarter%2Cthe%2520fourth%2520quarter%2520of%25202022.%5C%22%3ECommerce%20Department's%3C%2Fa%3E%20latest%20estimate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20all%20happened%20irrespective%20of%20interest%20rate%20cuts%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20Fisher%20said%2C%20suggesting%20there%20were%20more%20important%20levers%20driving%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20need%20rate%20cuts.%20The%20back%20half%20of%202022%20and%202023%20showed%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Fisher%2C%20investors%20have%20likely%20already%20priced%20in%20the%20impact%20of%20Fed%20rate%20cuts%20into%20the%20market%20anyway%2C%20given%20how%20widely%20discussed%20the%20Fed's%20policy%20moves%20are.%20Markets%20are%20betting%20on%20a%2060%25%20chance%20the%20Fed%20could%20cut%20interest%20rates%20at%20least%20100%20basis-points%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmegroup.com%2Fmarkets%2Finterest-rates%2Fcme-fedwatch-tool.html%3Fredirect%3D%2Ftrading%2Finterest-rates%2Fcountdown-to-fomc.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECME%20FedWatch%20tool%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%5BRates%5D%20don't%20have%20the%20effect%20on%20the%20overall%20economy%2C%20and%20by%20extension%20then