sewhere.%20In%20Karnataka%2C%20one%20of%20the%20very%20few%20states%20in%20India%20using%20this%20method%20extensively%2C%20that%20is%20literally%20what%20is%20unfolding%20on%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20459px)%2085vw%2C%20459px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10160846%2F1000016553.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22459%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10160846%2F1000016553.jpg%20968w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10160846%2F1000016553-242x300.jpg%20242w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10160846%2F1000016553-826x1024.jpg%20826w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-701002%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22569%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20elephant%20named%20%E2%80%9CThaneer%20Komban%E2%80%9D%20which%20died%20after%20being%20re-captured%20from%20the%20wild%20in%20Wayanad%20district%2C%20Kerala.%20Photo%3A%20Vinod%20Krishnan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20Thanneer%20%E2%80%93%20an%20elephant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fkochi%2Ftragic-death-of-thanneer-komban-after-circuslike-crowd%2Farticleshow%2F107395430.cms%5C%22%3Etranslocated%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Hassan%20to%20Bandipur%20Tiger%20Reserve%20in%20January%20this%20year%20after%20locals%20(as%20per%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fthesundaystandard%2F2024%2FFeb%2F04%2Fwild-elephant-captured-by-forest-dept-from-karnatakas-hassan-district-dies-of-heart-attack-when-released%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E)%20raised%20concerns%20of%20the%20animal%E2%80%99s%20crop-raiding%20behavior%20%E2%80%93%20ventured%20into%20neighboring%20Wayanad%20district%20in%20Kerala%20within%20a%20few%20weeks%20of%20his%20release.%20After%20protests%20by%20locals%2C%20the%20Kerala%20forest%20department%20decided%20to%20recapture%20the%20elephant.%20The%20operation%20lasted%20for%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fstates%2Fkerala%2F2024%2FFeb%2F04%2Fthanneerkomban-dies-experts-point-to-lapses-in-mission%5C%22%3E17%20hours%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Thanneer%20died%20in%20an%20elephant%20camp%20in%20Bandipur%2C%20where%20he%20was%20brought%20after%20the%20capture.%20Some%20claim%20the%20death%20resulted%20from%20shock%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fkochi%2Ftragic-death-of-thanneer-komban-after-circuslike-crowd%2Farticleshow%2F107395430.cms%5C%22%3Etrauma%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20others%20speak%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.mathrubhumi.com%2Fnews%2Fkerala%2Fseveral-pellet-mark-wounds-found-on-thaneer-komban-s-body-1.9295919%5C%22%3Einjuries%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20week%2C%20yet%20another%20radio-collared%20translocated%20elephant%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Belur%20Makhna%20%E2%80%93%20relocated%20from%20Hassan%20to%20Bandipur%2C%20also%20moved%20into%20Kerala.%20In%20the%20interactions%20that%20followed%2C%20a%20man%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.onmanorama.com%2Fnews%2Fkerala%2F2024%2F02%2F10%2Fwild-elephant-mananthavady-section-144.html%5C%22%3Edied%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20over%20ten%20days%2C%20close%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.onmanorama.com%2Fnews%2Fkerala%2F2024%2F02%2F14%2Fbelur-makhna-rrt-forest-darting-another-elephant-third-day.html%5C%22%3E200%3C%2Fa%3E%20staff%20of%20the%20Kerala%20forest%20department%20and%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fstates%2Fkerala%2F2024%2FFeb%2F16%2Fkerala-proposal-to-control-wildlife-population-draws-flak%5C%22%3E%20an%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fstates%2Fkerala%2F2024%2FFeb%2F16%2Fkerala-proposal-to-control-wildlife-population-draws-flak%5C%22%3E18-22-member%3C%2Fa%3E%20team%20from%20Karnataka%20were%20looking%20for%20the%20Belur%20Makhna%20to%20recapture%20him.%20The%20Kerala%20forest%20department%20also%20roped%20in%20sharpshooter%20Nawab%20Shafath%20Ali%20Khan%20for%20the%20operation.%20As%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbengaluru%2Fbelur-makhna-back-in-ktaka-as-kerala-tries-to-capture-it%2Farticleshow%2F107956927.cms%5C%22%3EFebruary%2024%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Belur%20Makhna%20is%20said%20to%20have%20reentered%20Karnataka.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20wait-and-watch%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20the%20negative%20impacts%20of%20translocating%20elephants%20have%20transpired%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cborder%20issue%E2%80%9D.%20Arikomban%20from%20Kerala%2C%20for%20example%2C%20in%20a%20day-long%20effort%2C%20was%20captured%20by%20over%20150%20forest%20staff%20and%20four%20%3Cem%3Ekumkis%3C%2Fem%3E%20(captive%20elephants%20that%20are%20trained%20to%20capture%20wild%20ones).%20The%20department%20moved%20him%20to%20Periyar%20Tiger%20Reserve%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Frogue-elephant-arikomban-captured-tamil-nadu-8647063%2F%5C%22%3Erecaptured%3C%2Fa%3E%20again%20after%20he%20moved%20into%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20Similarly%2C%20elephant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.onmanorama.com%2Fnews%2Fkerala%2F2023%2F01%2F09%2Fwild-elephant-pm2-tranquilised-forest-department.html%5C%22%3EPM2%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20post-translocation%2C%20was%20recaptured%20after%20it%20was%20found%20in%20Kerala.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStudies%20globally%20have%20shown%20how%20a%20scientifically%20carried%20out%20translocation%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20unobtrusive%20to%20a%20large%20extent%20%E2%80%93%20still%20leads%20to%20elevated%20physiological%20stress%20response%20for%20up%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.co.za%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.10520%2FEJC117293%5C%22%3E30%20days%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20release%20of%20the%20animal.%20T%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0003347206003460%5C%22%3Eranslocation%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20also%20generate%20various%20stressors%20at%20any%20stage%20of%20their%20execution%2C%20which%20have%20additive%20or%20cumulative%20effects%20on%20animals.%20So%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20surprising%20that%20these%20translocated%20animals%20are%20already%20stressed.%20Also%2C%20as%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC8800974%2F%5C%22%3Estudies%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20proved%20over%20the%20years%2C%20most%20translocated%20elephants%20move%20widely%20to%20return%20to%20their%20home%20range%20or%20try%20to%20establish%20home%20ranges%20in%20new%20areas.%20Interactions%20have%20always%20cropped%20up%20in%20these%20areas%2C%20as%20seen%20in%20the%20above-mentioned%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20translocation%20worth%20the%20effort%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20most%20of%20these%20translocation%20efforts%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FCoimbatore%2Fwild-elephant-karuppan-captured-in-talavadi-hill-translocated-to-thattakarai-forest-range-in-erode-division%2Farticle66747198.ece%5C%22%3E%20authorities%20declare%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FCoimbatore%2Fwild-elephant-karuppan-captured-in-talavadi-hill-translocated-to-thattakarai-forest-range-in-erode-division%2Farticle66747198.ece%5C%22%3Ecurfews%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20close%20down%20schools%20and%20colleges%20for%20a%20day%20or%20two.%20For%20many%20local%20communities%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fvillagers-intensify-protest-against-relocation-of-rogue-elephant-arikomban-from-idukki-to-parambikulam-wildlife-sanctuary-in-kerala-101681126167444.html%5C%22%3Eareas%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20capture%20and%20release%2C%20the%20stress%20is%20unbounded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20one%20of%20the%20elephants%20from%20Hassan%20was%20radio-collared%20and%20translocated%20to%20Bandipur%2C%20a%20scientist%20who%20was%20part%20of%20the%20operation%2C%20on%20anonymity%2C%20explained%3A%20%E2%80%9CMost%20of%20these%20translocated%20elephants%20make%20attempts%20to%20go%20back%20to%20their%20home%20range.%20We%20have%20also%20found%20interactions%20in%20areas%20of%20release.%20Locals%20now%20believe%20most%20of%20the%20radio-collared%20elephants%20to%20be%20those%20translocated%20from%20other%20areas.%20Hence%2C%20they%20protest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20IUCN%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fportals.iucn.org%2Flibrary%2Fsites%2Flibrary%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2F2003-089.pdf%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20guidelines%20for%20the%20translocation%20of%20African%20elephants%20states%20that%20communities%20around%20the%20release%20site%20should%20be%20consulted%20and%20kept%20informed%20for%20the%20long-term%20security%20of%20the%20translocated%20elephant.%20None%20of%20the%20forest%20departments%20in%20South%20India%20seek%20permission%20from%20locals%20in%20the%20release%20area%20before%20translocation.%20In%20Tamil%20Nadu%20last%20year%2C%20an%20elephant%20called%20Makhna%20was%20translocated%20for%20the%20second%20time%20and%20spent%20an%20agonising%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fstates%2Ftamil-nadu%2F2023%2FFeb%2F25%2Fmakhna-finally-findshome-after-200-km-ride-24-hours-on-truck-2550714.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DCOIMBATORE%253A%2520The%252045%252Dyear%252D%2Cits%2520release%2520in%2520their%2520localities.%5C%22%3E24%20hours%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20truck%20traveling%20200%20km%3A%20because%20locals%20in%20two%20separate%20areas%20protested%20against%20Makhna%E2%80%99s%20release%20near%20their%20villages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20almost%20all%20cases%20of%20translocation%20of%20elephants%20in%20these%20states%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20operation%20runs%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCaptures%20are%20expensive.%20The%20amount%20for%20tranquillisation%20and%20the%20transport%20of%20%3Cem%3Ekumkis%3C%2Fem%3E%20alone%20costs%20lakhs%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20forest%20official%20from%20Kodagu%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Karnataka%20spends%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fmysuru%2Fktaka-spends-rs-22-lakh-to-radio-collar-each-wild-jumbo%2Farticleshow%2F105830251.cms%5C%22%3ERs%2022%20lakh%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20radio-collar%20an%20elephant.%20According%20to%20some%20news%20reports%2C%20Kerala%20spent%20Rs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.onmanorama.com%2Fnews%2Fkerala%2F2023%2F08%2F05%2Fmission-arikomban-pt7-kerala-spend-rs33-lakh.html%5C%22%3E15.85%20lakh%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20translocate%20Arikomban%20and%20Rs%2017.32%20lakh%20in%20capturing%20and%20relocating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fkerala-forest-department-captures-rogue-elephant-pt-7-in-palakkad-renames-as-dhoni-1183697.html%5C%22%3EPT7%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20an%20elephant%20camp.%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20when%20rehoming%20some%20of%20the%20captured%20elephants%2C%20at%20times%2C%20spends%20Rs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FCoimbatore%2Fwork-to-construct-kraal-begins-at-chadivayal-elephant-camp%2Farticle25216940.ece%5C%22%3E10%20lakh%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20single%20%3Cem%3Ekraal%3C%2Fem%3E%20(an%20enclosure%20made%20to%20constrict%20and%20tame%20a%20wild%20elephant%20into%20submission).%20Authorities%20often%20spend%20more%20than%20Rs%202-3%20lakh%20on%20cage%20construction%20to%20transport%20the%20animal.%20Then%20comes%20the%20cost%20of%20transporting%20%3Cem%3Ekumkis%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20sometimes%2C%20up%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fkarnataka%2Foperation-jumbo-to-capture-wild-elephants-resumes-in-karnataka-2844812%5C%22%3Eeight%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20used%2C%20like%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fbengaluru-news%2Fkarnataka-forest-department-resumes-operation-jumbo-to-capture-wild-elephants-101704992262384.html%5C%22%3EKarnataka%E2%80%99s%20Operation%20Jumbo%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20aims%20to%20capture%20elephants%20and%20fix%20radio%20collars%20in%20Hassan%20district.%20Costs%20covering%20transport%2C%20earthmovers%20(numbers%20exceeding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FCoimbatore%2Foperation-black-to-capture-wild-elephant-begins-at-talavadi-hills-in-erode%2Farticle66369889.ece%5C%22%3E100%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20above%20at%20times)%2C%20staff%2C%20their%20food%20and%20stay%20for%20all%20the%20days%20spent%20searching%20and%20capturing%20an%20elephant%20%E2%80%93%20are%20additional.%20The%20cost%20of%20the%20upkeep%20of%20elephants%20captured%20for%20captivity%20is%20over%2011%20lakhs%20for%20one%20individual%20for%20a%20year%2C%20according%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.onmanorama.com%2Fnews%2Fkerala%2F2023%2F03%2F26%2Fkerala-government-spends-crores-wild-elephants.html%5C%22%3ERTI%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20all%20these%20go%20into%20a%20single%20capture%20and%20translocation%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20science%20behind%20identification%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20discussing%20plans%20for%20Operation%20Jumbo%2C%20a%20senior%20forest%20department%20official%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fbengaluru-news%2Fkarnataka-forest-department-resumes-operation-jumbo-to-capture-wild-elephants-101704992262384.html%5C%22%3Epress%20note%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20would%20start%20our%20operations%20in%20Belur%20taluk%20where%20more%20than%2050%20wild%20elephants%20had%20come.%20These%20wild%20jumbos%2C%20which%20came%20around%20two%20months%20ago%20into%20the%20Taluk%20area%2C%20have%20to%20be%20driven%20away%20to%20the%20elephant%20habitat.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20knee-jerk%20reaction%20to%20interactions%20and%20an%20unscientific%20method%20of%20identifying%20elephants%20for%20translocation%20has%20disrupted%20the%20lives%20of%20several%20elephants%20not%20responsible%20for%20interactions.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20has%20not%20addressed%20conflicts%20with%20humans%20on%20the%20ground.%20Locals%20have%20also%20expressed%20anger%20at%20such%20mishaps%20in%20the%20past.%20As%20in%20the%20case%20of%20elephant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.news18.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fa-case-of-mistaken-identity-locals-claim-karnataka-forest-dept-captured-wrong-elephant-as-rampage-continues-6773881.html%5C%22%3EBhaira%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Karnataka%E2%80%99s%20Chikkamagaluru%2C%20whose%20capture%20led%20to%20further%20protests%20by%20locals%20claiming%20the%20forest%20department%20picked%20the%20wrong%20elephant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20cases%2C%20people%20have%20mourned%20such%20unscientific%20decisions%2C%20like%20in%20the%20recent%20case%20with%20elephant%20Thanneer%2C%20where%20several%20expressed%20their%20grievances%20on%20social%20media.%20Vinod%20Krishnan%2C%20who%20has%20worked%20in%20Hassan%20for%20a%20decade%20handling%20human-elephant%20interactions%20and%20has%20observed%20Thaneer%20since%202018%2C%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CThaneer%20would%20simply%20walk%20away%20at%20the%20sight%20of%20any%20human%20being%20around.%20He%20kept%20to%20himself%20and%20did%20not%20harm%20anyone.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20public%20post%2C%20Krishnan%20recounted%20Thaneer%E2%80%99s%20story%20as%20an%20individual%2C%20as%20well%20as%20its%20behavior%20and%20life%3A%20who%2C%20in%20public%20memory%2C%20had%20passed%20on%2C%20being%20remembered%20as%20just%20another%20featureless%20%E2%80%9Crogue%E2%80%9D%20elephant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fcontent%2F647543%2Fneed-restore-elephant-corridors.html%5C%22%3E2017%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20interacted%20with%20locals%20near%20Karnataka%E2%80%99s%20Cauvery%20Wildlife%20Sanctuary%20after%20elephants%20raided%20over%2055%20farms%20in%20a%20single%20day.%20They%20demanded%20barricades%2C%20the%20timely%20presence%20of%20the%20forest%20department%20during%20the%20crisis%2C%20and%20compensation.%20No%20one%20spoke%20of%20capture.%20However%2C%20that%20has%20changed%20now.%20The%20use%20of%20translocation%20as%20mitigation%20has%20doubled%20since%202014%20after%20authorities%20captured%2F%20translocated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fwith-human-elephant-conflict-taking-more-lives-on-both-sides-stakeholders-are-split-over-a-sustainable-solution%2Farticleshow%2F68337524.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E22%3C%2Fa%3E%20wild%20elephants%20from%20Hassan%20based%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.peepli.org%2Fstories%2Fthe-elephants-must-go%2F%5C%22%3Erecommendations%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20scientists%20and%20members%20of%20the%20then%20Karnataka%20Elephant%20Task%20Force.%20Unfortunately%2C%20this%20also%20triggered%20dependence%20and%20a%20pattern%20in%20locals%2C%20who%20have%20since%20been%20requesting%20capture%20as%20the%20only%20solution%20to%20interactions%20across%20Karnataka%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20being%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Froundglasssustain.com%2Fconservation%2Felephant-translocation%5C%22%3E%20evidenced%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20mitigation%20measure%2C%20often%20leading%20to%20more%20interactions%2C%20this%20solution%20has%20been%20used%20in%20reckless%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fbangalore%2F74-elephants-captured-rehabilitated-in-sakleshpura-and-belur-taluks-of-karnataka-8080952%2F%5C%22%3E%20frequency%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20which%20is%20expensive%2C%20highly%20stress-inducing%20and%20risky%20to%20humans%20and%20elephants%20but%20has%20yielded%20(mostly)%20a%20cycle%20of%20misfortunes%3A%20conflict-%20capture%20%E2%80%93%20translocation-conflict%20%E2%80%93%20conflict-recapture.%20Repeat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20resorting%20to%20intrusive%20solutions%20like%20translocation%20is%20rarely%20adopted%20by%20states%20that%20witness%20more%20interactions%20than%20Karnataka%2C%20such%20as%20Assam%20and%20West%20Bengal.%20Banerjee%20says%20that%20investing%20in%20short%20term%2C%20band-aid%2C%20tech-only%20solutions%20(such%20as%20radio%20collaring%20and%20translocations)%20for%20long-persisting%20issues%20like%20human-wildlife%20interactions%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20always%20help.%20Addressing%20the%20local%20driving%20factors%20%E2%80%93%20political%2C%20social%2C%20and%20cultural%20%E2%80%93%20is%20essential.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COne%20needs%20to%20go%20a%20bit%20deeper%20to%20understand%20the%20roots%20through%20which%20these%20narratives%20were%20set%20and%20put%20into%20motion.%20We%20are%20solution-centric%2C%20trying%20to%20find%20new%20techs%20to%20solve%20an%20apparent%20unsolvable%20problem.%20The%20assumption%20of%20wildlife%20conflict%20management%20is%20that%20we%20cannot%20treat%20socio-political%20causes%20and%20find%20newer%20solutions%20(or%20tech)%20to%20pacify%20the%20situation.%20Both%20elephants%20and%20people%20who%20live%20around%20these%20elephants%20are%20the%20losers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.eletellnow.wordpress.com%5C%22%3EGana%20Kedlaya%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20environment%20reporter%20based%20in%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710067500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10160754%2F1000016556.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthree-states-to-work-together-to-address-the-elephant-in-the-room%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20ongoing%20human-elephant%20interaction%20crisis%20in%20South%20India%2C%20the%20role%20of%20translocation%20and%20its%20impact%20needs%20attention.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthree-states-to-work-together-to-address-the-