spects%20of%20the%20world.%20The%20next%20essay%20will%20touch%20upon%20this%20topic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUsha%20Alexander%20trained%20in%20science%20and%20anthropology.%20After%20working%20for%20years%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20she%20now%20lives%20in%20Gurugram.%20She%E2%80%99s%20written%20two%20novels%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0The%20Legend%20of%20Virinara%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0Only%20the%20Eyes%20Are%20Mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710050720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112000%2FIMG_2968.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Four-insatiable-quest-for-fire%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Continuing%20to%20increase%20our%20dependency%20on%20these%20fossils%20in%20any%20way%20makes%20literally%20no%20Earthly%20sense.%20We%20must%20instead%20imagine%20a%20system%20that%20moves%20away%20from%20burning%20fossils%2C%20altogether%2C%20rap%C2%A0idly%20and%20completely.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Four-insatiable-quest-for-fire%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'To%20Kill%20a%20Tiger'%20Chronicles%20a%20Father's%20Pursuit%20of%20Justice%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20Strength%20of%20Women%20Around%20Him%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10111355%2FTo-Kill-a-Tiger-02.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20glitzy%20Oscars%20scene%2C%20where%20gowns%20and%20tuxedos%20steal%20the%20show%2C%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20best%20documentary%20contenders%2C%20including%20Nisha%20Pahuja%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ETo%20Kill%20A%20Tiger%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20explore%20family%2C%20social%20justice%2C%20book%20banning%2C%20war%20and%20politics.%20Pahuja%E2%80%99s%20two-hour%20feature%20stands%20out%2C%20chronicling%20a%20father%E2%80%99s%20unwavering%20pursuit%20of%20justice%20for%20his%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20sat%20down%20to%20write%20a%20review%20of%20this%20heart-rattlingly%20urgent%20documentary%3Cem%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fnational%2Fjharkhand-13-year-old-girl-killed-for-resisting-rape-attempt-in-godda%5C%22%3Enews%20%3C%2Fa%3Etrickled%20down%20about%20yet%20another%20killing%20of%2013-year-old%20girl.%20She%20was%20allegedly%20killed%20in%20Jharkhand%E2%80%99s%20Godda%20district%20after%20she%20resisted%20an%20attempt%20of%20rape%20by%20two%20men%20aged%2021%20who%20have%20confessed%20to%20committing%20the%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20irony%20weighs%20on%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20vast%20media%20universe%2C%20stories%20of%20sexual%20assault%20often%20fade%20away%2C%20lost%20in%20overloaded%20legal%20processes%20or%20swallowed%20by%20toxic%20masculinity.%20Yet%2C%20%3Cem%3ETo%20Kill%20A%20Tiger%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20cinematic%20documentary%2C%20purposefully%20unveils%20real-life%20stories%2C%20urging%20broader%20attention%20to%20the%20rampant%20epidemic%20of%20misogynistic%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETending%20to%20the%20rice%20fields%2C%20Ranjit%20%E2%80%93%20the%20doting%20father%20to%20his%20daughter%2C%20the%20victim%20of%20a%20sexual%20assault%20in%202017%20%E2%80%93%20shares%20a%20poignant%20revelation%20towards%20the%20end%20of%20the%20film.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20once%20told%2C%20%E2%80%98You%20can%E2%80%99t%20kill%20a%20tiger%20by%20yourself%2C'%E2%80%9D%20recounts%20Ranjit%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20I%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%98I%E2%80%99ll%20show%20you%20how%20to%20kill%20a%20tiger%20all%20by%20yourself.%E2%80%99%20And%20so%2C%20I%20did.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20sets%20up%20the%20narrative%20arc%20of%20the%20tale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Emotional%20journey%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForged%20over%20the%20course%20of%20eight%20years%2C%20the%20documentary%2C%20winner%20of%20more%20than%2020%20awards%20at%20festivals%20around%20the%20world%2C%20highlights%20the%20pervasive%20and%20deeply%20rooted%20nature%20of%20male%20violence%20against%20females%20ingrained%20in%20the%20fabric%20of%20our%20society.%20How%20does%20one%20tell%20such%20a%20story%3F%20Caught%20in%20the%20spotlight%2C%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20stance%20captivates%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20Srijan%20Foundation%2C%20an%20NGO%20dedicated%20to%20sensitising%20men%20and%20boys%20about%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights.%20They%20see%20in%20Ranjit%20a%20symbol%20for%20their%20cause%2C%20a%20beacon%20of%20inspiration%20for%20other%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20Delhi-born%20Canadian%20director%20Nisha%20Pahuja%20says%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3ETo%20Kill%20a%20Tiger%20%3C%2Fem%3Eactually%20started%20off%20as%20an%20entirely%20different%20film.%20That%20film%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESend%C2%A0Us%20Your%20Brother%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20was%20a%20more%20pointed%20and%20direct%20exploration%20of%20Indian%20masculinity.%20The%20focus%20of%20the%20original%20work%20was%20Mahendra%20Kumar%2C%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20activist%20who%20has%20a%20key%2C%20albeit%20minor%2C%20role%20in%20the%20film.%E2%80%9D%20However%2C%20as%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20story%20emerged%20from%20a%20programme%20led%20by%20Mahendra%20in%20Jharkhand%2C%20the%20director%20recognised%20its%20potential%20as%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20backbone%2C%20with%20his%20work%20and%20personal%20life%20adding%20a%20broader%20context%20to%20the%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETo%20Kill%20a%20Tiger%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3Echarts%20the%20emotional%20journey%20of%20an%20ordinary%20man%20thrown%20into%20extraordinary%20circumstances%20%E2%80%93%20a%20father%20whose%20love%20for%20his%20daughter%20forces%20a%20social%20reckoning%20that%20will%20reverberate%20for%20years%20to%20come.%20The%20allure%20of%20this%20approach%20stemmed%20from%20its%20simplicity.%20It%20offers%20a%20continuity%20to%20a%20rich%20body%20of%20works%20that%20Pahuja%20has%20undertaken%20over%20two%20decades%2C%20like%20Pahuja%E2%80%99s%20short%20film%20for%20%3Cem%3EGlobal%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20investigative%20news%20and%20current%20affairs%20programme%2016%C3%979%20%E2%80%98Indian%20Bus%20Outrage%E2%80%99%2C%20investigating%20flaws%20in%20the%20justice%20system%20in%20India%20following%20the%20brutal%202012%20gang%20rape%20and%20murder%20of%20a%20young%20woman%20on%20a%20bus%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20It%20was%20a%20recipient%20of%20an%20Amnesty%20International%20media%20award%20for%20Canadian%20journalism%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FmC6-igJ_WWM%3Fsi%3D6mZeRndBdacBfDeV%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPahuja%20approached%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20complex%20situation%20with%20a%20keen%20understanding%20of%20its%20layered%20sensitivity.%20With%20prior%20experience%20directing%20films%20in%20India%2C%20notably%20%3Cem%3EThe%20World%20Before%20Her%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2012)%20that%20juxtaposed%20the%20competition%20among%20women%20aspiring%20to%20be%20Miss%20India%20with%20Hindu%20nationalists%20defending%20their%20beliefs%20(awarded%20Best%20Canadian%20Feature%20at%20the%20Hot%20Docs%20Canadian%20International%20Documentary%20Festival)%2C%20she%20was%20mindful%20not%20to%20take%20sides%20in%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20documentary%E2%80%99s%20narrative%20fabric%2C%20intimate%20scenes%20from%20village%20gatherings%20reveal%20a%20spectrum%20of%20perspectives%2C%20featuring%20voices%20even%20from%20the%20fathers%20of%20the%20accused.%20Yet%2C%20as%20the%20legal%20proceedings%20persist%2C%20a%20faction%20of%20villagers%20resorts%20to%20coercive%20tactics%20against%20Ranjit%20%E2%80%93%20employing%20emotional%20manipulation%2C%20proffering%20bribes%20and%20escalating%20to%20threats%20of%20arson%20and%20murder.%20This%20mounting%20tension%20culminates%20in%20an%20increasing%20animosity%20directed%20at%20the%20film%20crew%20earnestly%20documenting%20these%20unfolding%20and%20unsettling%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20narrative%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPahuja%E2%80%99s%20husband%2C%20Mrinal%20Desai%2C%20wields%20the%20camera%20like%20a%20poet%E2%80%99s%20pen.%20He%20deftly%20captures%20the%20village%E2%80%99s%20serenity%2C%20meandering%20through%20its%20tranquil%20spaces%20and%20deciphering%20the%20unspoken%20dialect%20of%20gazes%20%E2%80%93%20all%20the%20while%20encapsulating%20the%20hidden%20subterranean%20explosiveness%20simmering%20beneath%20the%20narrative%E2%80%99s%20surface.%20As%20if%20drawing%20inspiration%20from%20the%20locale%2C%20a%20mining%20town%20famed%20for%20its%20rich%20mineral%20veins%2C%20the%20cinematographer%20moulds%20haptic%20images%2C%20extracting%20their%20nuanced%20meanings%20and%20tensions.%20The%20cinematic%20shots%20in%20the%20labyrinth%20of%20courts%20in%20Ranchi%20reminds%20one%20of%20his%20early%20work%20in%20Chaitanya%20Tamhane%E2%80%99s%20Marathi-language%20courtroom%20drama%2C%20%3Cem%3ECourt%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2014).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cinematic%20narrative%20commences%20with%20Ranjit%20articulating%20the%20profound%20experience%20of%20welcoming%20his%20daughter%2C%20Kiran%2C%20into%20the%20world.%20He%20cloaks%20her%20in%20the%20entirety%20of%20his%20affection%2C%20challenging%20the%20notion%20that%20love%20transcends%20the%20confines%20of%20material%20reality.%20With%20her%20penchant%20for%20narrative-driven%20films%2C%20Pahuja%20crafts%20intricately%20woven%20worlds%20that%20captivate%20with%20their%20visual%20splendour%20%E2%80%93%20a%20close-up%20of%20Kiran%20braiding%20her%20hair%20with%20colourful%20ribbons%20%E2%80%93%20reminiscent%20of%20the%20Spanish%20filmmaker%20Isabel%20Coixet.%20More%20so%2C%20it%20is%20particularly%20apparent%20in%20her%20silent%20portrayal%20of%20Kiran%E2%80%99s%20mother%2C%20highlighting%20her%20steadfast%20silent%20presence%20and%20the%20nuanced%20dynamics%20of%20her%20relationship%20with%20her%20husband%20Ranjit.%20The%20deliberate%20manner%20in%20which%20she%20guides%20and%20supports%20him%20during%20his%20moments%20of%20vulnerability%20underscores%20her%20inherent%20strength.%C2%A0%20Wrestling%20with%20the%20profound%20intricacies%20of%20human%20existence%20remains%20a%20constant%20in%20Pahuja%E2%80%99s%20exploration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20National%20Film%20Board%20of%20Canada-funded%20documentary%2C%20her%20storytelling%2C%20delicately%20rendered%2C%20possesses%20a%20distinctly%20feminine%20and%20sensual%20allure.%20That%20made%20me%20think%20of%20Jane%20Campion%2C%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20contemporary%20filmmakers%2C%20and%20her%20classic%20short%20%E2%80%93%20a%20tightly%20controlled%20nine-minute%20drama%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EPeel%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1982)%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Piano%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1993)%20and%20more%20recent%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Power%20of%20the%20Dog%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2021).%20Though%20a%20tale%20of%20the%20father%E2%80%99s%20pursuit%2C%20this%20film%20is%20predominantly%20concerned%20with%20female%20characters%20struggling%20to%20be%20heard%2C%20recognised%20and%20understood.%20The%20intricacies%20of%20other%20figures%20in%20the%20tale%20%E2%80%93%20namely%2C%20the%20Ward%20Member%2C%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20wife%20Jaganti%2C%20and%2C%20most%20notably%2C%20his%20daughter%20Kiran%20%E2%80%93%20unfold%20in%20delicate%20layers.%20While%20Kiran%20undeniably%20survives%20a%20brutal%20crime%2C%20her%20character%20transcends%20simplistic%20victimhood%2C%20revealing%20nuanced%20facets%20that%20enrich%20the%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEthics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20Pahuja%E2%80%99s%20narrative%20ethics%20govern%20her%20art.%20%E2%80%9CDiscussing%20morality%20without%20considering%20the%20ethics%20of%20filming%20a%20survivor%2C%20especially%20a%20child%2C%20would%20be%20a%20lapse%20on%20my%20part.%20Initially%20hiding%20Kiran%E2%80%99s%20identity%20complied%20with%20Indian%20law%20and%20felt%20right%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20reflects.%20However%2C%20grappling%20with%20the%20prevailing%20cultural%20stigma%2C%20she%20questions%2C%20%E2%80%9CBy%20not%20showing%20her%2C%20am%20I%20perpetuating%20the%20bias%20I%20critique%3F%20Yet%2C%20imposing%20my%20perspective%20on%20a%20vulnerable%20child%20feels%20unjust.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20is%20emerging%20to%20be%20a%20thorny%20issue.%20Anna%20M.M.%20Vetticad%2C%20author%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Adventures%20of%20an%20Intrepid%20Film%20Critic%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20points%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.himalmag.com%2Fculture%2Fto-kill-a-tiger-oscars-india-rape-pocso%5C%22%3Eethical%20and%20legal%20violations%3C%2Fa%3E%20inherent%20in%20the%20making%20of%20the%20film.%20The%20issue%20of%20filming%20a%20minor%20rape%20victim%20makes%20it%20vulnerable%20for%20the%20filmmaker%2C%20given%20the%20stringent%20guidelines%20under%20the%20Protection%20of%20Children%20from%20Sexual%20Offences%20(POCSO)%20Act%202012.%20The%20victim%E2%80%99s%20parent%E2%80%99s%20permission%20does%20not%20suffice%2C%20one%20has%20to%20get%20a%20directive%20from%20a%20special%20court%20if%20it%20deems%20in%20its%20view%20that%20such%20disclosure%20aligns%20with%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20the%20child%20involved.%20Meanwhile%20another%20Canadian%20filmmaker%2C%20Leena%20Manimekalai%2C%20has%20patently%20dismissed%20the%20film%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FLeenaManimekali%2Fstatus%2F1746228215671079068%5C%22%3Ea%20classic%20example%20of%20a%20settler%20colonist%20gaze%20on%20an%20indigenous%20child%20survivor%20of%20gang%20rape%20in%20a%20developing%20country%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20documentary%2C%20Kiran%20existed%20as%20both%20a%20child%20and%20a%20survivor.%20Today%20in%20her%2020th%20year%2C%20Kiran%20is%20so%20much%20more.%20She%20stands%20tall%20and%20looks%20out%20to%20a%20brighter%20future%20and%20wonders%20about%20falling%20in%20love%20and%20what%20she%20will%20tell%20her%20beloved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20also%20my%20hope%20that%20collectively%20we%20empower%20her%20and%20support%20her%20healing%20as%20part%20of%20this%20film%E2%80%99s%20journey%20in%20the%20world%20%E2%80%93%20a%20journey%20with%20impact%20at%20its%20heart%2C%20and%20one%20that%E2%80%99s%20being%20planned%20carefully%20and%20strategically%20with%20lawyers%2C%20documentary%20impact%20strategists%2C%20therapists%20and%20an%20advisory%20council%20made%20up%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20and%20human%20rights%20organisations%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Pahuja.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20growing%20list%20of%20executive%20producers%20that%20are%20attached%20to%20this%20film%20including%20Dev%20Patel%2C%20Mindy%20Kailing%2C%20poet%20Rupi%20Kaur%2C%20Dr%20Atul%20Gawande%20and%20Priyanka%20Chopra%20Jonas%2C%20to%20ensure%20this%20story%20does%20what%20it%20can%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20the%20distressing%20news%20of%20yet%20another%20assault%20on%20a%2013-year%20old%20girl%20in%20the%20same%20region%20filtering%20through%2C%20the%20sickening%20irony%20piles%20up%2C%20each%20layer%20adding%20a%20punch%20to%20the%20gut%20within%20the%20narrative%20of%20this%20documentary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENarendra%20Pachkh%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C3%A9%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Ed%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C3%A9%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Eis%20a%20critic%20and%20writer%20who%C2%A0splits%20his%20time%20between%20Toronto%2C%20London%20and%20Geneva.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710049542000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10111355%2FTo-Kill-a-Tiger-02.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fto-kill-a-tiger-nisha-pahuja%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nisha%20Pahuja's%20Oscar-nominated%20cinematic%20documentary%20purposefully%20unveils%20real-life%20stories%2C%20urging%20broader%20attention%20to%20the%20rampant%20epidemic%20of%20misogynistic%20violence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fto-kill-a-tiger-nisha-pahuja%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BHow%20Many%20100s%20You%20Got%3F%26quot%3B%3A%20Full%20Text%20Of%20Shubman%20Gill%2C%20Jonny%20Bairstow%20Sledge%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EStar%20India%20batter%20Shubman%20Gill%20and%20England%20middle-order%20batter%20Jonny%20Bairstow%20had%20a%20heated%20exchange%20during%20the%20fifth%20and%20final%20Test%20between%20both%20sides%20at%20Dharamshala%20on%20Saturday.%20On%20Day%20three%2C%20England's%20ageless%20pace%20wonder%20James%20Anderson%20had%20become%20the%20first%20pacer%20ever%20to%20reach%20700%20Test%20wickets.%20One%20of%20his%20two%20victims%20during%20India's%20first%20innings%20was%20Gill%2C%20who%20had%20scored%20a%20fine%20century%2C%20concluding%20what%20could%20be%20a%20breakthrough%20Test%20series%20after%20a%20string%20of%20low%20scores%20on%20a%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20before%20Gill%20had%20reached%20his%20century%2C%20he%20exchanged%20some%20words%20with%20the%2041-year-old%20pacer.%20When%20asked%20in%20the%20post-day%20press%20conference%2C%20Gill%20had%20said%20as%20quoted%20by%20Wisden%20on%20his%20exchange%20with%20Anderson%2C%20%26quot%3B%20I%20think%20it%20would%20be%20better%20for%20both%20of%20us%20to%20keep%20that%20chat%20in%20private.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Jonny%20came%20out%20to%20bat%20during%20England's%20second%20innings%20when%20they%20were%20tasked%20with%20cutting%20down%20a%20lead%20of%20259%20runs%20by%20India%2C%20Bairstow%20tried%20to%20enquire%20Gill%20about%20what%20he%20said%20to%20Anderson%20during%20their%20exchange.%20The%2024-year-old%20batter%20boldly%20revealed%20that%20he%20told%20Anderson%20to%20retire.%20When%20Bairstow%20tried%20to%20remind%20Gill%20that%20Anderson%20got%20him%20soon%20after%20the%20exchange%2C%20the%20subject%20of%20conversations%20turned%20to%20centuries%20made%20during%20the%20series%2C%20where%20Gill%20had%20an%20upper%20hand%20over%20Bairstow%2C%20scoring%20two%20centuries%20as%20compared%20to%20none%20by%20the%20English%20batter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere%20is%20how%20the%20conversation%20went%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EGill%20on%20fire%20today..%3Cbr%3E%5CnAfter%20this%20argument%20bairstow%20was%20given%20out%20!%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FzQ1dQM8jyP%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FzQ1dQM8jyP%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20khushi%20(%40khushich277)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fkhushich277%2Fstatus%2F1766354333338312879%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%209%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EJonny%20Bairstow%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20did%20you%20say%20to%20Jimmy%20about%20him%20retiring%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShubman%20Gill%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20told%20him%20he%20should%20retire%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBairstow%3A%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20he%20got%20you%20out%20next%20ball%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGill%3A%20%26quot%3BSo%20what%3F%20How%20many%20times%20has...%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBairstow%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20just%20asking%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGill%3A%20%26quot%3BHe%20can%20get%20me%20out%20after%20my%20100%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBairstow%3A%20%26quot%3B100%20per%20cent%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGill%3A%20%26quot%3BHow%20many%20100s%20%5Bdo%20you%20have%5D%20this%20series%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBairstow%3A%20%26quot%3BHow%20many%20have%20you%20scored%2C%20full%20stop%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20players%20were%20trying%20to%20get%20under%20each%20others'%20skins%20during%20a%20crucial%20point%20in%20the%20match%20and%20the%20trick%20went%20in%20India's%20favour%20as%20just%20four%20balls%20later%20Kuldeep%20Yadav%20trapped%20Bairstow%20leg-before%20wicket%20for%2039%20in%2031%20balls%20and%20England%20went%20on%20to%20lose%20the%20game%20by%20an%20innings%20and%2064%20runs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGill%20had%20a%20fine%20series%20with%20the%20bat%2C%20ending%20as%20the%20second-highest%20run-getter%20with%20452%20runs%20in%20nine%20innings%20at%20an%20average%20of%2056.5%2C%20with%20two%20centuries%20and%20two%20fifties.%20His%20best%20score%20was%20110.%20Bairstow%20on%20the%20other%20hand%20flopped%20big%20time%2C%20managing%20just%20238%20runs%20in%2010%20innings%20at%20an%20average%20of%2023.8%2C%20with%20the%20best%20score%20of%2039.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20winning%20the%20toss%20and%20opting%20to%20bat%20first%2C%20the%20visitors%20were%20bundled%20out%20for%20218%20in%20their%20first%20innings%2C%20with%20Zak%20Crawley%20(79%20in%20108%20balls%2C%20with%2011%20fours%20and%20a%20six)%20top-scored%20for%20England%2C%20Jonny%20Bairstow%20(29)%2C%20and%20Joe%20Root%20(26)%20the%20only%20notable%20contributors%20with%20the%20willow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKuldeep%20Yadav%20(5%2F72)%20and%20Ravichandran%20Ashwin%20(4%2F51)%20topped%20the%20bowling%20charts%20for%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710049380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2F5uvumid8_rohit_625x300_10_March_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Findia-vs-england-2024%2Fhow-many-100s-you-got-full-text-of-shubman-gill-jonny-bairstow-sledging-war-5210636%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Shubman%20Gill%20and%20Jonny%20Bairstow%20engaged%20in%20an%20ugly%20war%20of%20wards%20on%20Day%203%20of%20the%20Dharamsala%20Test.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Designer%20Donatella%20Versace%20rescued%20from%20lift%2